        -:   55:// The default evaluator performs an "arithmetic" operation on two input arrays.
        -:   56:// Given input arrays 'lhs' and 'rhs' and binary functor 'func', 
        -:   57:// the sparse destination array 'dst' is evaluated as follows:
        -:   58://   if lhs(i,j) and rhs(i,j) are present, dst(i,j) = func(lhs(i,j), rhs(i,j))
        -:   59://   if lhs(i,j) is present and rhs(i,j) is null, dst(i,j) = func(lhs(i,j), 0)
        -:   60://   if lhs(i,j) is null and rhs(i,j) is present, dst(i,j) = func(0, rhs(i,j))
